                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="20046" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 4 Oct 2006 05:08:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has a rather fundamental root cause: PropertyEditors themselves are usually not serializable. We have deliberately made them transient and allowed for restoring them afterwards, for example through re-applying PropertyEditorRegistrars. This is the approach WebFlow takes; I cannot see any immediate alternative...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20052" author="aantono" created="Wed, 4 Oct 2006 07:47:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Juergen, we are also using WebFlow, but the problem comes into play when the redirect happens, it sends the 302 directly to a page, so there is nothign in between to reapply the editors.  So once the jsp page gets to the spring:bind tag and creates the BindStatus object, that&apos;s the first place the BindingResult is accessed, and the BeanWrapper instance gets recreated.  So maybe it would be possible to add some code in the BindTag to supply the custom editors.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
